# device-registry — consolidated environment reference
#
# This file documents every environment variable used by the service.
# It is NOT loaded at runtime. Use the per-environment files instead:
#
#   .env.development.template  →  copy to .env.development  (local dev)
#   .env.staging.template      →  copy to .env.staging      (staging)
#   .env.production.template   →  copy to .env.production   (production)
#
#   .env.{env}.json  —  primary source per environment (Azure Key Vault)
#   .env.{env}       —  flat fallback, auto-synced from JSON on startup
#
# All keys are canonical (no environment prefix). Each environment gets
# its own file, so prefixes are unnecessary.
#
# Loading order (first non-empty value wins):
#   1. .env.{NODE_ENV}.json  (Azure Key Vault — authoritative)
#   2. .env.{NODE_ENV}       (flat fallback / local override)
#   3. config/environments/{env}.js  (legacy alias shims, will be removed)

